ess_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aAn increasingly important and appealing concept for school renewal is that of school as community. While community holds multiple promises for schools, little is known about the practice of community in schools. This collection furthers our understanding about the nature of school community, its practice in public schools, and the role of leadership in this practice. Of particular importance is the question of how community can be created and sustained in K–12 public schools with highly diverse populations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aCommunity and schoolzUnited States. 0aSchool management and organizationzUnited States. 4aEducation : Education. 7aEDUCATION / Educational Policy & Reform / General.2bisacsh1 aBeck, Lynn G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCapper, Colleen A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCroningerg, Robert G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFinkelstein, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFurman, Gail, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFurman, Gail, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGallucci, Chrysan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoldman, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHafner, Madeline M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeyes, Maureen W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMawhinney, Hanne B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOsterman, Karen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO’Hair, Mary John, econtrib